WAVE SPIN

wave_spin is the spin channel of the qu-septit native compute substrate
spin is the body's rotational orientation: positive spin rotates forward through the wave cycle, negative spin rotates backward
spin determines the direction of phase advance and which interactions reinforce versus cancel

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_phase2.zc

the 7 properties of wave_spin itself:
1 ENERGY zero
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one: this channel holds spin primarily
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING half
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB carry_spin
hold the spin value of every body, each body's spin as one cell

VERB direct_phase_advance
during each pulse, spin determines whether a body's phase increments forward or decrements backward
positive-spin bodies advance, negative-spin bodies retreat, zero-spin bodies hold

a spin channel is what gives bodies direction
without spin, all bodies would oscillate symmetrically and constructive interference between distant bodies would be impossible
spin makes the substrate's wave physics directional, which is what allows information to travel
